cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper discusses privacy implications and proposes a privacy-preserving solution for sharing location traces. 
- cs.SI (Signal Processing) is also likely as the paper proposes treating spatiotemporal trajectories as space-time signals to lower computational complexity. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper discusses user mobility modeling and achieving high precision and recall. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses reducing data dimensionality to facilitate offloading computational tasks. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on networking or internet architecture, but rather on privacy-preserving mobility modeling on smartphones.
